The course is closely associated with a specific international criminal law moot court, e.g. ICCMCC. During the first phase, the students prepare the written memorials of parties. In the second phase oral pleadings take placeObjectives/eesmärkid:  To gain a deeper theoretical understanding of international criminal law and to get practical litigation experience while participating in the international criminal law moot courtLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	Student has deep knowledge of international criminal law 2.	Student applies principles and rules of international criminal law and international law correctly 3.	Student conducts research on international criminal law issue and is capable of adequately evaluating the relevance of sources 4.	Student uses techniques of legal argumentation and present his or her arguments convincingly 5.	Student can present his or her oral arguments confidently and is capable of answering questions convincingly  6.	Student, with his or her team, establishes goals for independent and shared research activities.  7.	Student speaks and writes in English on a high level
